<subSubSection id="3D77771444B307420F9A1A53A0549B84" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="type locality">
<paragraph id="16A60D650C2D0937923B8F974A8C2073" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type locality.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="37902FD1250E202CA4741E881E76BDDA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Phia Oac National Park, Cao Bang, Vietnam.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8A4B0314192CDDC7D107FD6B8DBA362F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="type material">
<paragraph id="36095C3919D36148A4FBE37EC85C529D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type material.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0EF11522EC7E018C3F5B13E070F9CF3D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="DBC485883043881BACA964371D24529B" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Holotype</emphasis>
(male, CNC): Vietnam, Cao Bang, Phia Oac Nat. Park, summit rd., behind upper FIT, 
<geoCoordinate id="FF218EDE204198FF63747F555753D174" degrees="22" direction="north" minutes="36" orientation="latitude" precision="1" seconds="21.60" value="22.606">22°36'21.60&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="AFCAD7839D5578BB52C9CEE011F50C9E" degrees="105" direction="east" minutes="52" orientation="longitude" precision="1" seconds="19.20" value="105.872">105°52'19.20&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
, 1600 m, mat. secondary forest, fogging standing dead tree w/ orange fungus, 7-17.V.2019, A. Brunke &amp; H. Schillhammer, CNC1898850 [typed label] / 
<taxonomicName id="36D3A1BF50F7BB0C014EDE1A7C8D28B9" authorityName="Brunke" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bolitogyrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bolitogyrus nigropolitoides" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropolitoides">
<emphasis id="4B1C497B0DE74311E3EC349CAAE101B8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Bolitogyrus nigropolitoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Brunke, des. Brunke, 2021 [red label]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="641307AC8BABFC526131145194816B82" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B8491112B80B84475BC6A32E84E338CD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6776FBE4A58160F2572830276D43CB93" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The species epithet refers to the similar species 
<taxonomicName id="00E1D28AFFFD39F7692685DE166009AE" family="Staphylinidae" genus="B." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="B. nigropolitus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="nigropolitus">
<emphasis id="CD3C131E336A5C125E6A747DFD3DCD6C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B. nigropolitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Sichuan, China.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="289B70167E1B58B7490A1BA0A851E851" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="92ABF7F261853685C019570C51756CA6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="780577875E1555BAC348A4A8308A0C59" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Within the Electus group (for diagnosis, see 
<bibRefCitation id="783F0B2EB75FAF11B1ED0D2250BA877C" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.423.7536" author="Brunke, A" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 113" refId="B2" refString="Brunke, A, Solodovnikov, A, 2014. A revision of the Neotropical species of Bolitogyrus Chevrolat, a geographically disjunct lineage of Staphylinini (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). ZooKeys 423: 1 - 113, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.423.7536" title="A revision of the Neotropical species of Bolitogyrus Chevrolat, a geographically disjunct lineage of Staphylinini (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.423.7536" volume="423" year="2014">Brunke and Solodovnikov 2014</bibRefCitation>
): abdomen entirely dark; head without deeply impressed punctures; lateral face of hind tibia bicolored, distal half distinctly paler than darkened part of hind femur; antennomere 5 subquadrate, 6 distinctly transverse (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="537B39B6D78E4E953AD3F7D8DBB947E4" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. A-C habitus of Bolitogyrus erythrurus (Kraatz) A non-type, Panama B syntype, &quot; Nova Grenada &quot; C non-type, &quot; Nova Grenada &quot; D, E pronotum, lateral view D B. viridescens Brunke E B. pseudostrigifrons Brunke F antenna of B. nigropolitoides Brunke. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.5 mm (D-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1096.80773.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672695" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1F</figureCitation>
); paramere slightly longer than median lobe, in ventral view median lobe not visible; paramere with apical part broadly rounded to apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="95A6D7406DEFB32353424C21E8569B0F" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Male genitalia A, C, E Bolitogyrus strigifrons (Wendeler) B, D, F B. pseudostrigifrons Brunke G, I B. nigropolitus Smetana H, J B. nigropolitoides A, B, G, H median lobe in lateral and C, D ventral view. E, F, I, J inner face of paramere, apex. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-D, G, H); 0.1 mm (E, F, I, J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1096.80773.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672696" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2J</figureCitation>
); median lobe in lateral view with smaller subapical expansion (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C98309FA3B6CBE8FC43FFA4876EE4980" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Male genitalia A, C, E Bolitogyrus strigifrons (Wendeler) B, D, F B. pseudostrigifrons Brunke G, I B. nigropolitus Smetana H, J B. nigropolitoides A, B, G, H median lobe in lateral and C, D ventral view. E, F, I, J inner face of paramere, apex. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-D, G, H); 0.1 mm (E, F, I, J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1096.80773.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672696" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A2BDE8696FBE429236EAED05A13E159F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="7B76AD394959F4A52A15EC8986250E93" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D71748BC216ED957A4624C72255D0DAB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Measurements ♂ (
<emphasis id="594B2C922C7705E7C790563232362740" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">n</emphasis>
= 1): HW/HL 1.30; PW/PL 1.17; EW/EL 1.12; ESut/PL 0.85; PW/HW 1.09; forebody length 4.5 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C5738A2AFF2AED15A2CE41C6DFDA522D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4048A60FBB4D25CE0A573FF37DD54439" authorityName="Smetana" authorityYear="2000" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bolitogyrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bolitogyrus nigropolitus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropolitus">
<emphasis id="27F8E10856CF4A77C32436BCCCB10B3C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Bolitogyrus nigropolitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2CF739E9CF469DBB8CAEC37177D354CA" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Male genitalia A, C, E Bolitogyrus strigifrons (Wendeler) B, D, F B. pseudostrigifrons Brunke G, I B. nigropolitus Smetana H, J B. nigropolitoides A, B, G, H median lobe in lateral and C, D ventral view. E, F, I, J inner face of paramere, apex. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-D, G, H); 0.1 mm (E, F, I, J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1096.80773.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672696" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A684F3B5CF74DC1846BD1DCCF2237359" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Male genitalia A, C, E Bolitogyrus strigifrons (Wendeler) B, D, F B. pseudostrigifrons Brunke G, I B. nigropolitus Smetana H, J B. nigropolitoides A, B, G, H median lobe in lateral and C, D ventral view. E, F, I, J inner face of paramere, apex. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-D, G, H); 0.1 mm (E, F, I, J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1096.80773.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672696" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2I</figureCitation>
) except: antennae shorter, antennomere 5 subquadrate, 6 distinctly transverse (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A7A51B0EAC9C39E6F043FB0D718AEB4E" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. A-C habitus of Bolitogyrus erythrurus (Kraatz) A non-type, Panama B syntype, &quot; Nova Grenada &quot; C non-type, &quot; Nova Grenada &quot; D, E pronotum, lateral view D B. viridescens Brunke E B. pseudostrigifrons Brunke F antenna of B. nigropolitoides Brunke. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.5 mm (D-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1096.80773.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672695" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1F</figureCitation>
); pronotum slightly less transverse; elytral slightly longer; paramere slightly longer than median lobe, in ventral view median lobe not visible with paramere in situ; paramere with apical part broadly rounded to narrower apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="41559A77A3CFF3A2599691715D784B44" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Male genitalia A, C, E Bolitogyrus strigifrons (Wendeler) B, D, F B. pseudostrigifrons Brunke G, I B. nigropolitus Smetana H, J B. nigropolitoides A, B, G, H median lobe in lateral and C, D ventral view. E, F, I, J inner face of paramere, apex. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-D, G, H); 0.1 mm (E, F, I, J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1096.80773.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672696" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2J</figureCitation>
); median lobe in lateral view with subapical expansion much smaller (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="82AD61338D6278C2411716EF1D3F5EDC" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Male genitalia A, C, E Bolitogyrus strigifrons (Wendeler) B, D, F B. pseudostrigifrons Brunke G, I B. nigropolitus Smetana H, J B. nigropolitoides A, B, G, H median lobe in lateral and C, D ventral view. E, F, I, J inner face of paramere, apex. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-D, G, H); 0.1 mm (E, F, I, J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1096.80773.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672696" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2012AB6DE4F68370F080ABE8CAF0CB6B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="4BD9656952122F0C140518A070BE3A3F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C38C2560480EBD8D883CA256CA567E8A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">This species is known only from Phia Oac National Park in northern Vietnam, though it likely occurs at similar elevations in neighboring Yunnan, China and elsewhere in northern Vietnam east of the Red River.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D5915374D1AE69681BDA16C8D9622BA9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="bionomics">
<paragraph id="5E2CA7AD2196EC77337C6F8B3355D876" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Bionomics.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="130F4B3E3087E2B6F394F66748F83657" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">The holotype was pyrethrin-fogged from a dead standing tree, bearing orange-fungal fruiting bodies.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E405A46AD87AA5C584815537555C2D76" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="caesareus group">
<paragraph id="07D66351745F1479E1C37AB6D6981D45" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Caesareus group</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
